MBOMBELA- Two accidents involving at least six vehicles are causing heavy delays on the R40. The one accident, involving four vehicle, occurred around 16:30, bringing traffic to an almost complete standstill. The details on the second accident is still vague. According to information to Lowvelder’s disposal, the accident occurred near Riverside Mall on the R40. This is a developing story and Lowvelder will keep you updated as soon as more information becomes available. Consider alternative routes if you are travelling in either direction on the R40. Motorists are urged to remain patient. Also read: Mamba appeal to be heard in High Court